ZH: 今天早上，我迟到了，因为我的闹钟没有响铃声。
EN: This morning, I was late because my alarm clock did not make a ringing sound.

ZH: 每天早上，我都设置手机的闹钟来提醒我起床。
EN: Every morning, I set my phone's alarm clock to remind me to get up.

ZH: 在图书馆里，我们被要求关掉手机，因为铃声会打扰其他人。
EN: In the library, we are asked to turn off our phones because the ringing sound can disturb others.

ZH: 当我接听电话时，听到了一个朋友捣乱的铃声。
EN: When I answered the phone, I heard a prank ringing sound from a friend.

ZH: 在电影院里，一名观众的手机突然响起，打扰了整个场面。
EN: In the cinema, a viewer's phone suddenly started ringing, disturbing the entire scene.

ZH: 我喜欢设置短信铃声为轻快的旋律。
EN: I like to set my text message ringtone to a cheerful melody.

ZH: 老师要求学生上课时将手机调成静音模式，以避免铃声干扰学习。
EN: The teacher asks students to put their phones on silent mode during class to avoid the ringing sound disrupting learning.

ZH: 晚上睡觉时，我关掉了手机的铃声，以免被电话打扰。
EN: I turned off the ringtone of my phone when I went to sleep, so that I wouldn't be disturbed by calls.

ZH: 当地铁停在地下站台时，你会听到一个铃声来提醒乘客上下车。
EN: When the subway stops at an underground platform, you will hear a ringing sound to remind passengers to get on and off.

ZH: 我的手机铃声设置为嘟嘟声，因为它让我轻松愉快。
EN: I set my phone ringtone as a beep sound because it makes me feel relaxed and happy.

ZH: 在一座山里，我听到从远处传来的铃声，是羊群在放牧。
EN: In a mountain, I heard ringing sounds coming from a distance, it was a herd of sheep grazing.

ZH: 当我的耳朵发出铃声时，我知道自己需要去看医生。
EN: When my ears make a ringing sound, I know I need to go see a doctor.

ZH: 在中国的年底，你会听到很多庆祝铃声，象征着新年的到来。
EN: At the end of the year in China, you will hear many celebratory ringing sounds, symbolizing the arrival of the New Year.

ZH: 当我找到我的丢失的钥匙时，我听到钥匙链上的铃声。
EN: When I found my lost keys, I heard the ringing sound from the keychain.

ZH: 在农村地区，你会听到农民在田地里工作时铃声悠扬的歌声。
EN: In rural areas, you will hear the melodious singing with the ringing sound of farmers working in the fields.

ZH: 在大街上散步时，你可以听到街头艺人弹奏吉他时的铃声。
EN: While walking on the street, you can hear the ringing sound of street artists playing guitar.

ZH: 我的手机接收到新信息时，会发出铃声提醒我查看。
EN: My phone makes a ringing sound to remind me to check when it receives a new message.

ZH: 在室内演唱会上，歌迷会通过挥舞手中的荧光棒和发出的铃声表达热烈欢呼。
EN: During indoor concerts, fans express their enthusiastic applause through waving fluorescent sticks and making ringing sounds.

ZH: 银行给顾客发放号码牌时，会通过铃声进行呼叫。
EN: Banks use ringing sounds to call customers when distributing queue numbers.

ZH: 在十字路口，行人通过听到红绿灯的铃声，确定是否可以过马路。
EN: At intersections, pedestrians determine whether they can cross the road by listening to the ringing sound of traffic lights.
